                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 5.26,
                                "byte_start": 89870,
                                "byte_stop": 110977,
                                "text": "Second case, I hope you thought that one was technical."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 5.26,
                                "stop": 12.547,
                                "byte_start": 110977,
                                "byte_stop": 140130,
                                "text": "This one is called Zuni School District versus the Department of Education."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 12.547,
                                "stop": 27.072,
                                "byte_start": 140130,
                                "byte_stop": 198226,
                                "text": "Now, there is a federal statute again and what this federal statute says is, it says that \u201cif in fact there are a lot of costs that the federal government is making a local school district incur.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 27.072,
                                "stop": 33.753,
                                "byte_start": 198226,
                                "byte_stop": 224975,
                                "text": "For example maybe there is a lot of federal land nearby or maybe there is an army-base and they have to educate the children."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 33.753,
                                "stop": 44.143,
                                "byte_start": 224975,
                                "byte_stop": 266458,
                                "text": "So, the federal government has made it harder for the local school district to raise money for its expenses or to pay money for the education."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 44.143,
                                "stop": 52.181,
                                "byte_start": 266458,
                                "byte_stop": 298641,
                                "text": "Will Then the federal government will give them some money they will write them a check, say, it was for a million dollars."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 52.181,
                                "stop": 68.995,
                                "byte_start": 298641,
                                "byte_stop": 365932,
                                "text": "Well, the federal government says in this statute now if we give you the million dollars to the School District for this, the state cannot just take the million away by reducing their own aid to the School District by a million; they can\u2019t do that."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 68.995,
                                "stop": 83.513,
                                "byte_start": 365932,
                                "byte_stop": 423924,
                                "text": "But, then someone worked out that suppose they have what\u2019s called an equalization program in the state where they try to keep per-pupil expenditure about the same in all the school districts, suddenly, there\u2019ll be a school district with an extra million dollars and that might make them the riches."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 83.513,
                                "stop": 95.103,
                                "byte_start": 423924,
                                "byte_stop": 470317,
                                "text": "So, they should be able to offset in that situation and so they wrote the statute to say but, in that situation they can offset provided there is an equalization program."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 95.103,
                                "stop": 97.502,
                                "byte_start": 470317,
                                "byte_stop": 479930,
                                "text": "Well, what\u2019s an equalization program?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 97.502,
                                "stop": 119.485,
                                "byte_start": 479930,
                                "byte_stop": 567911,
                                "text": "So, the statute sets up a method for measuring that and it says basically the method consists of list all the school districts in order of per-pupil expenditure, look at the top one, look at the bottom one and if it\u2019s less than 25% difference in what they\u2019re spending per-pupil then you\u2019ve got an equalization program."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 119.485,
                                "stop": 131.766,
                                "byte_start": 567911,
                                "byte_stop": 617021,
                                "text": "So far so good but then they add an instruction, the added instruction is to say when you make that list don\u2019t put in the outliers, well, what\u2019s an outlier?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 131.766,
                                "stop": 154.272,
                                "byte_start": 617021,
                                "byte_stop": 706987,
                                "text": "An outlier and this is what\u2019s called the disregard instruction, says that, when comparing the highest and lowest per-pupil expenditures the \u201csecretary shall disregard school districts with per-pupil expenditures above the 95th percentile or below the 5th percentile of such expenditures.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 154.272,
                                "stop": 157.39,
                                "byte_start": 706987,
                                "byte_stop": 719526,
                                "text": "Now, we get to the question in the case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 157.39,
                                "stop": 175.528,
                                "byte_start": 719526,
                                "byte_stop": 792041,
                                "text": "When the Secretary of Education was administering this statute he would lineup all the school districts and then when you try to see what to disregard, he looked to the top 5% of pupils by number and pupils by bottom, that\u2019s the top and the bottom."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 175.528,
                                "stop": 187.487,
                                "byte_start": 792041,
                                "byte_stop": 839898,
                                "text": "Now, some school districts have worked out they\u2019re going to get more money if they say, you shouldn\u2019t have done that, what you\u2019re supposed to do is disregard 5% of the school districts, not 5% of the pupils."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 187.487,
                                "stop": 190.655,
                                "byte_start": 839898,
                                "byte_stop": 852541,
                                "text": "Well, which should it be?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 190.655,
                                "stop": 205.143,
                                "byte_start": 852541,
                                "byte_stop": 910533,
                                "text": "The secretary says, I want to tell you two things, first, we\u2019ve done it my way, pupils for 35 years now, I wrote this statute in draft and sent it to Congress and there are no exceptions and I have excellent reasons."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 205.143,
                                "stop": 215.82,
                                "byte_start": 910533,
                                "byte_stop": 953165,
                                "text": "My reason of course is imagine that you had a school district, a state would say 20 school districts and suppose that of the 20."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 215.82,
                                "stop": 231.137,
                                "byte_start": 953165,
                                "byte_stop": 1014500,
                                "text": "For example, two of them accounted for half of the pupils in the state, the rest were rural, and suppose that two one was at the top and one was at the bottom, well, 5% of school districts, you\u2019ll be disregarding half of the pupils, those who are not outliers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 231.137,
                                "stop": 239.271,
                                "byte_start": 1014500,
                                "byte_stop": 1046997,
                                "text": "So, I want to do it my way by pupils, it makes sense historically, it makes sense in terms of purpose but what about the language."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 239.271,
                                "stop": 245.634,
                                "byte_start": 1046997,
                                "byte_stop": 1072492,
                                "text": "At this point, all of us I think, all nine of us worked out that that language is a little difficult."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 245.634,
                                "stop": 262.182,
                                "byte_start": 1072492,
                                "byte_stop": 1138634,
                                "text": "So, we\u2019ve gone into the language in depth in the opinion for those who are interested you can read about that language and five of us, a majority in the opinion I am announcing conclude that the language permits the Secretary\u2019s interpretation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 262.182,
                                "stop": 265.905,
                                "byte_start": 1138634,
                                "byte_stop": 1153576,
                                "text": "Four of us conclude that it doesn\u2019t and they dissent."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 265.905,
                                "stop": 273.884,
                                "byte_start": 1153576,
                                "byte_stop": 1185446,
                                "text": "Well, by this greater than before so we favor the Secretary in our holding and we affirm the judgment of the Tenth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 273.884,
                                "stop": 276.791,
                                "byte_start": 1185446,
                                "byte_stop": 1197044,
                                "text": "Justice Stevens has written a concurring opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 276.791,
                                "stop": 281.001,
                                "byte_start": 1197044,
                                "byte_stop": 1213971,
                                "text": "Justice Kennedy has written a concurring opinion which Justice Alito has joined."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 281.001,
                                "stop": 289.756,
                                "byte_start": 1213971,
                                "byte_stop": 1248975,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has written a dissenting opinion in which the Chief Justice and Justice Thomas have joined and in which Justice Souter has joined as to Part I."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 289.756,
                                "stop": 292.023,
                                "byte_start": 1248975,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Souter has written a dissenting opinion."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
